# Loki Mode -- environment for docker compose
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values:
#   cp .env.example .env
# Then run:
#   docker compose run loki start prd.md
# Edit .env and re-run any time -- compose reloads it automatically, so you
# never retype a long `docker run -e ...` command.
#
# .env is gitignored. NEVER commit real keys or tokens.

# ===========================================================================
# Auth -- pick ONE method
# ===========================================================================

# Option 1 (default, recommended): Anthropic API key.
# Get one at https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-key-here

# Option 2 (Claude Code Max/Pro subscribers, no API key): host OAuth.
# Leave ANTHROPIC_API_KEY unset and instead mount your Claude Code credentials.
# See DOCKER_README.md "Option 2: host OAuth" for the one-line export command
# and the docker-compose volume to uncomment. Nothing goes in this file for
# Option 2 -- the token is mounted as a file, never an env var.

# ===========================================================================
# Optional provider overrides (Codex / Cline / Aider are bring-your-own-CLI
# in Docker; the image ships only the Claude Code CLI by default)
# ===========================================================================
# LOKI_PROVIDER=claude

# ===========================================================================
# Optional runtime knobs
# ===========================================================================
# LOKI_MAX_ITERATIONS=20
# LOKI_DASHBOARD=true
# LOKI_DASHBOARD_PORT=57374

# GitHub (for issue-mode `loki start owner/repo#123` and PR creation)
# GITHUB_TOKEN=
# GH_TOKEN=
